  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "/kind bug\r\n\r\nRight now we do not validate PV updates so admin can update `PV.Spec.PersistentVolumeSource` at any time. Kubernetes has no facility to reflect this update - it won't magically re-mount an existing volume to e.g. a different NFS server. IMO the PersistentVolumeSource to be read-only and set to stone once created.\r\n\r\n@kubernetes/sig-storage-bugs @kubernetes/sig-api-machinery-bugs ",
